ENTRY            F1533   20251111   20260305   20260305       F106
SUBENT        F1533001   20251111   20260305   20260305       F106
BIB                 14         35
TITLE      Total cross sections for the reactions 10,11,12Be+28Si
           and 14B+28Si
AUTHOR     (Yu.G.Sobolev,V.V.Samarin,Yu.E.Penionzhkevich,
           S.S.Stukalov,M.A.Naumenko)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB,4RUSDBU,4RUSMIF)
           (4RUSRUS) Department of Nuclear Physics, Voronezh State
           University
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,110,014609,2024)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRevC.110.014609
FACILITY   (ISOCY,4ZZZDUB) U-400M cyclotron and ACCULINNA fragment
           separator were used.
INC-SOURCE The primary 15N beam with an energy of 49.7 A MeV was
           focused on the production 9Be target. The secondary
           beam of fragmentation reaction products was formed
           and purified by the magnetic system of the fragment
           separator.
SAMPLE     DeltaE detector (natural Si, 790 mu-m thick) was used
           as a target.
DETECTOR   (SI) A system of deltaE detectors was used.
           (CSICR) The scintillation detectors of the spectrometer
           registered prompt gamma quanta and neutrons.
METHOD     (TOF,GSPEC) 4pi method with CsI(Tl) gamma
           spectrometer was used.
           (TRN) Measurements were conducted both with the target
           and without the target to measure the background.
CORRECTION An empirical correction 'eta' (sigmaR=sigmaR/eta) was
           introduced. It takes into account not only the
           anisotropy of neutron emission but also the
           contribution of the elastic breakup channel which is
           not accompanied by gamma radiation.
ADD-RES    The effective matter radii of the 11,12Be and 14B
           nuclei were determined.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No source of uncertainty is given.
STATUS     (APRVD) Entry was approved by Dr. Yu.G. Sobolev.
HISTORY    (20251111C)
